this requirement can be done in two ways.
- by creating BindingPointerFromPropertyValue to serve as source for bindings and add to same contract
- by creating new contract which uses same as previously BindingPointerFromPropertyValue as source.

which one is correct mainly depends on two things. 
- how much self dependent and controlled it needs to be
- how much one wishes for simplified application API. 

&lt;big&gt;&lt;b&gt;NOTE&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/big&gt;
to preanswer one question that will be definitely asked. add support for "parent.info"?

databinding API has no intention of ever supporting more than one property per redirection like in this case "parent.info" bacause it is not only cumbersome, it is a real bad karma for refactoring. it is only supported by databinding solurions that didn't think ahead. 

that said, API is designed to allow it with very little trouble. if anyone needs treatment like this he can simply wrap &lt;b&gt;chain_property&lt;/b&gt; to preresolve whole chain. 

note that implementation of this has 0 chance of ever being accepted for multitude of reasons</property>
