                                <property name="label" translatable="yes">&lt;b&gt;Class description (hover over label to see source)&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;small&gt;binding pointer serves as object that can point to source by having controlled reference handling and defines how data updates are dispatched. but, probably 
most important feature is chaining support and its control signals

&lt;span color='red'&gt;property&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;reference_type&lt;/b&gt; - STRONG/WEAK define how reference is treated. with WEAK no reference is made, with STRONG exactly 1 reference is created
and being locked until binding pointer refers to it. no matter how complex chaining, it will always be 1 reference. can only be specified on pointer creation
&lt;span color='red'&gt;property&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;update_type&lt;/b&gt;- PROPERTY/MANUAL defines if object is dispatching its own signals or reliance goes straight to custom handling. if binding object is 
chained onto another binding object &lt;b&gt;update_type&lt;/b&gt; will not return its own value, but rather value of the chained pointer. can only be specified on pointer 
creation
&lt;span color='red'&gt;property&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;data&lt;/b&gt; - can hold 3 types of values (object reference, SELF, null). when value is set signals are dispatched (change source in this demo to get exact
picture of how/when/how. note that it is probably better to use signals than notify for this property as it provides more information
&lt;span color='red'&gt;signal&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;data_changed&lt;/b&gt; is probably the only one needing explanation. when binding pointer declares &lt;b&gt;update_type&lt;/b&gt; as MANUAL it is emission of this signal is
expected to notify when bindings need update for that source. note that signal has (BindingPointer, string) parameters where second can be used to fine 
grain what needs to be updated
&lt;span color='red'&gt;virtual method&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;get_source()&lt;/b&gt; resolves end of chain pointer is pointing at. &lt;b&gt;this method plays vital role in later chapters and will be explained then&lt;/b&gt;

other signals are simply better left to visual representation. just change source for binding pointer and listbox will represent what was happening and when

&lt;/small&gt;DEMO (change source and watch how binding pointer reacts)</property>
