                                <property name="label" translatable="yes">&lt;b&gt;Class description (hover over label to see source)&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;small&gt;binding contract extends the Binding Pointer by adding possibility to handle property bindings on specified source by adding/removing. bindings can either
be added/removed as single entity or as group. their addition checks if reference for specified binding already exists or not. if binding is present its lock
counter is increased by 1, if not binding is added to the contract. when removing binding does not get removed if lock counter didn't reach 0. this and group
handling makes it available for groups to share bindings with no worry

&lt;span color='red'&gt;property&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;is_valid&lt;/b&gt; - specifies validity of source data it points to. each property binding can introduce its own condition and result of &lt;b&gt;is_valid&lt;/b&gt; is cumulative
of all active bindings in contract. this is useful to have automatic handling of buttons like "Apply". note that contract can add other conditions with state objects
&lt;span color='red'&gt;property&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;length&lt;/b&gt; - number of bindings in contract
&lt;span color='red'&gt;property&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;suspended&lt;/b&gt; - contract suspension disables all data traffic contract is specifying (useful to temporarily disable gui refresh when processing)
&lt;span color='red'&gt;property&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;default_target&lt;/b&gt; - automatic binding pointer that is specified as target with &lt;b&gt;bind_default&lt;/b&gt; which simplifies handling of data binding when contract
handles more than one property between two objects. this also guaratees single point of maintenancy to change target just as &lt;b&gt;data&lt;/b&gt; does it for source
&lt;span color='red'&gt;property&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;can_bind&lt;/b&gt; - true if currently binding is possible, false if not
&lt;span color='red'&gt;signal&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;contract_changed (contract)&lt;/b&gt; - sent whenever contract is disolved or renewed
&lt;span color='red'&gt;signal&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;bindings_changed (contract)&lt;/b&gt; - sent whenever bindings are added or removed

&lt;b&gt;NOTE! API to add bindings is exactly the same as PropertyBinding with one exception of adding validity function parameter
WARNING! do not use "data" notification as check point. use signals&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/small&gt;</property>
